<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p>The Public Health Sciences minor offers undergraduate students a foundation of knowledge for those who plan to enter the field of public health immediately following graduation and for those planning to earn an advanced degree in Public Health or a related field including medicine, nursing, and dentistry.</p>
<p>Subscribe to the Public Health Minor mailing list at <a href="https://health.ucdavis.edu/phs/education/minor_mail.html">PHS Minor listserv</a>.</p>
<p>Contact the <a href="mailto:PHSInstAffairs@ucdavis.edu">Public Health Science advising team</a>.</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
<requirementstext name="Requirements">
<![CDATA[
<p>To successfully complete the minor, students must complete 20 units of coursework. The required 20 units will be split between required core courses and additional elective courses. Only one lower-division course can be applied and only one course can overlap between the major and the minor.</p>
